Prime Probe Tool

Overview

This directory contains the implementation of a Prime Probe tool using Vulkan and CUDA. The source files included in this project are:

vulkan_buffer.cpp

prime_probe.cu

instruction_chain.cu

instruction_chain.h

Makefile

The tool leverages Vulkan for buffer management and CUDA for executing the Prime Probe cache attack.


Requirements

To compile and run this tool, ensure your system has the following dependencies installed:

GCC: gcc-11.4, g++-11.4

CUDA: CUDA 12.6

Vulkan: Vulkan 1.2.131


Vulkan Installation

Vulkan must be installed following the official Vulkan tutorial. Detailed instructions can be found here:

https://vulkan-tutorial.com/

Compilation and Execution

To build the project, simply run:

make

Once compiled, you can execute the tool using:

./prime_probe


Configuration

Users can modify the following parameters in prime_probe.cu:

LOOP_NUM: Determines the number of Prime Probe iterations.

TIME_BUF_SIZE: If LOOP_NUM is set greater than 4000, you must increase TIME_BUF_SIZE to expand the memory buffer for storing time measurements.


Code Reference

For further details on implementation, refer to the code comments in the source files.


